        <h1>Homemade Cheese</h1>
       
        <div class="recipe-details">
         <img src="homemade.jpeg" alt="Homemade Cheese" class="recipe-image">
            <div class="ingredients">
                <h2>Ingredients:</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>1 liter whole milk</li>
                    <li>2 tbsp lemon juice</li>
                    <li>Cheesecloth for straining</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="instructions">
                <h2>Instructions:</h2>
                <ol>
                    <li>Bring the milk to a boil in a pot.</li>
                    <li>Add lemon juice and stir until the milk curdles.</li>
                    <li>Strain the mixture through a cheesecloth to separate the curds from the whey.</li>
                    <li>Press the curds into a block and let it set for 2-3 hours.</li>
                    <li>Use as desired in recipes or eat fresh.</li>
                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>
